The Lagos State Police Command has confirmed the arrest of four persons involved in the killing of a sound engineer by motorists over N100 change. According to reports gathered, the victim identified as David, and his friend was attacked and burnt after a misunderstanding over the N100 balance with one of the commercial motorcyclist. Lagos State Police Public Relations Officer, Benjamin Hundeyin, confirmed the incident via a tweet on Sunday stating that they would be prosecuted. -Advertisement- He wrote, “I can authoritatively confirm that all the perpetrators of this heinous crime have been arrested. “They will all be prosecuted. Say no to jungle justice!”